node.text:
It’s Hydrangea Season…

The kitchen’s half-clean and I got new barstools! So I’m celebrating. 🥂

We haven’t had barstools in months! (Can you believe Philly sold ours?🤨 Truth: I don’t have a good record with chairs, he sold our kitchen table chairs, too- they all complain that neither were comfortable.)

Barstools are so hard to find! I’ve been looking for over a year!
I finally found these from @chernyshbrothers ✨

“We” wanted something with a low back that would fit under the counter, they needed to be easy in/easy out, well-made, comfortable (and of course, I wanted them to look good!)

These are perfect!
Hand-made, solid oak and 
beautiful quality.  I love the woven natural rope seat and the oak finish is just right!

They are light, comfortable AND…
They passed the test!! We all love them!

I’ve linked them in my #liketoknowit 
(You can follow me there!) 
And I’ll add a swipe up in stories!

P.S…

When together you have cute initials...you love a monogram.
We go together like “S”alt and “P”epper!💁‍♀️

Now that we are nearly finished with our bedroom suite update, i had to have the most luxurious towels I could find. 
And @matouklinens makes the very best!! 

I love a simple white towel- I chose the Auberge monogram because they are modern and bold, yet subtle and so luxurious! Then I mixed the Kiran waffle towels for texture and together they are the perfect finishing touch!

I love working with local New England companies, @matouklinens has produced quality linens right here in Fall River for 100 years! 

Swipe through to see more details, and I’ve shared my sources in #liketoknowit you can follow me there! I’ll add a swipe up in my stories!

Happy Weekend !! The sun is finally back?🌞

node.text:
Breezy…

There is nothing like summer on Cape Cod! One of my favorite things about living by the coast is the consistent summer breeze off Buzzards Bay.
Our windows are always open and our curtains are always swaying in the breeze.

But one of my least favorite things for my Virgo/ A-type visual-self is to constantly be adjusting them! 😬#ad

When I worked on our bedroom suite window treatments with @TheShadeStore we kept this in mind. 
I wanted a light and airy fabric, unlined so they would move with the breeze. They suggested the Tribeca Track Rod and with pinch pleats on the Luxe Linen drapes. This system would allow the curtains to dance but would give them the structure to fall right back into place perfectly! They would open and close easily and always look great. 

I love waking up to filtered light but wanted the option for privacy. I used a mix of woven wood for privacy and linen for filtered light. Our Luxe Linen Roman Shades on the smaller windows have just a touch of detail, a beautiful mohair bouclé trim!
I love how they are subtle and unfussy yet offer a touch of soft refinement!! Swipe to see! 

We couldn’t be happier with them!

And, working with @TheShadeStore was a breeze😉

So many of you ask for the details:
We used:
•Luxe Linen drapes and Roman Shades (color Beige)
•Roman flat shades in Luxe Linen Beige with Capella Mohair trim (color Sand)
•Waterfall Woven wood shades, Seaview (color Salt)

I’ve shared more details on the blog, linked in bio!

node.text:
Welcome To Camp-Bridge…

You guys followed along as we celebrated Nathalie’s graduation from Cambridge University this weekend. 
#sponsored

First, a little background: A few weeks ago Nathalie started planning the party and looked for housing- Of course, nothing was available on Cape Cod, Fourth of July weekend. So Plan A was to scatter the crowd of 16 at local friends and family’s homes. But, that plan didn’t sit right with her- she worried about getting people home once the night was over, she felt like the crowd would be disjointed. The twins hatched a plan to do a glamping-thing in our clearing that overlooks the salt marsh. Plan B.
I totally loved the idea. They were so excited to be able to camp out all together for 4 days.

I immediately went to @walmart and started pulling all the pieces together. 

I found tents, inflatable mattresses, cozy bedding and pillows and lanterns. I even made Welcome Bags for each guest which included a beach towel, a bath towel, a hand towel and wash cloth. Then I added all the little necessities. The bags worked perfectly for getting to and from the outdoor showers and to use as beach bags. All with one click through @walmart ✨ I was so impressed with all the options from #walmarthome to make this weekend unforgettable for them.

Swipe through for a tour of the four tents and to see how cozy and inviting we were able to make them. The set-ups were AWESOME! I am showing all the different ways to use the tents, one without the shade cover, one completely buttoned up (it rained!!) We added a power strip to each tent so the kids could charge their phones, we had mason jars with twinkle lights by each door so they could see in the night, and we had an overhead lantern with a remote control to shut it off from bed. I opted for matching everything to make it uniform and I used vintage chairs and side tables in each tent!
The last slide is a walk through the camp at sunrise, so you can really get a feel for it!
I’m sharing more in stories with links to everything! And, shopping @walmart through LIKEtoKNOW.it is so easy! Just copy and paste this link:

node.text:
Afterglow…

It was a hell of a Fourth of July/Graduation party.🎇

The kids spent yesterday morning cleaning up and packing to go, and believe it or not (if you watched my stories this weekend 😬) the house is completely pulled back together-laundry and all!

(So many of you are asking for a glimpse at the tents, I’ll share them tomorrow! It’s been a very busy weekend!)

Looking back on this weekend;
18 young adults traveled from all over the country to celebrate with Nathalie for 4 days. Watching them pull it all together (planning, food shopping, cooking all the meals and cleaning up along the way, then hosting a beautiful party on Sunday night!) despite the weather and sleeping in tents-no fighting, laughing all the way told me:

1: they have a lot of experience at parties🤔 and
2: they are all engaging, kind and positive humans!
(“Show me your friends and I will tell you who you are.”)✨

Posting this shot from last night, the Fifth of July, when the skies finally cleared and it was quiet here, again. 
Look close, I caught twin sparkly fireworks all the way back there in the distance. 💗💙

node.text:
Retreat from the Storm…

If you have been watching my stories the last few days you know that pretty much my whole house is in party-mode right now and there are only two spots that are “unaffected by the storm.” 

This in one of them so I’ve been hiding out in here, I’m sharing this view because If I turn around and look behind me at the porch, it’s one of the areas AFFECTED.😬

(I heard a guest look in here and say,
“It’s just too pretty to go in there!”😆)

It’s been raining for days, and it’s freezing cold but that hasn’t dampened the spirits of these kids! They’ve been swimming in the ocean, taking outdoor showers and running between the tents and the house like “what rain?”

I may have to call FEMA in when this is over, but for now it’s all good!

Rain or Shine…

Our guests have been trickling in since last night and I have to say, whatever the weather, everyone is having a great time. 

We opted for pizza night instead of grilling tonight. Everyone slept in the old bunkroom (my new office😶) last night. We are definitely working through all the plans, A through Z!

These kids are so easy going and helpful—and….It is so nice to have a houseful again!! 

Swipe to see a few views of our front entryway last night, before the rain-
door wide open and
I wouldn’t have it any other way!

Batten Down the Hatches…

The storm’s moving in and we are still trying to figure out exactly where the 8 arriving guests will be sleeping tonight😬 All four tents are up, but….

We actually came up with Plan A, B and C so I’m not that worried!

I, on the other hand, will be sleeping here!🤭

(I just this second stopped to enjoy the new rug I got in here from @stofferhome 🧡 The pattern and colors are so pretty! I love how cozy it makes this room feel and it’s beautiful underfoot! This is the Rosemarie rug!)
